    {
      "id": "1446405824464556032",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-12-05T07:40:21.473+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Thanks @tnt for the hint!\n\nFrom the DRM:\n\n> 1. Possible repairs to metal antenna nodes, which have a high via count or antenna ratio.\n>   a. Add an NCOMP/Substrate diode for NMOS gate, PCOMP/Nwell diode for PMOS gate.\n>   b. Break the metal close to the gate and jog the metal to an upper metal level.\n\nSo instead of:\n\n```\ndiode      = nplus.and(comp)\n```\n\nI would do:\n\n```\nn_diode    = nplus.and(comp).not(nwell)\np_diode    = pplus.and(comp).and(nwell)\ndiodes     = n_diode || n_diode\n```\n\n(deep nwell not considered.)\n\nDoes that look reasonable to you?",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [
          {
            "id": "1423020172595298314",
            "name": "Mod",
            "color": null,
            "position": 1
          }
        ],
        "avatarUrl": "2025-12_media/3c7c17f3225f6e56f4dccd83f14383f2-73F83.png"
      },
